OL,3,CWhat is happening in Cuba?
OL,5,FMeanwhile, the US has been bound by
OL,6,Flaw since the 90s that ties sanctions
OL,7,Fto political change and states
OL,8,Fembargoes can be raised only when a
OL,9,Ftransition government is in power.
OL,11,FSince Castro took power in 1959, the
OL,12,Fcountry has faced several crises, from
OL,13,Fa full US-enforced isolation of the
OL,14,Fisland during the Cold War, to the
OL,15,Floss of a major economic support with
OL,16,Fthe collapse of the Soviet Union.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/19
